<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE SPEED AXLES: SPICER D135-S,
        F155-S, F170-S SERIES - CLEAN AND INSPECT - INSPECT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INSPECT</title>
        <para>Prior to reassembly, inspect parts for signs of excessive wear or damage. Replacement of these parts can
            prevent premature failure and costly downtime.
        </para>
        <para>Bearing surfaces should be inspected for pitting, excessive wear, or overheating (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401428">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1401428" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401428" filename="../figg14/G1401428.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 28. Bearing Surface Inspection</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect gears for wear or damage. Replace gears that are pitted, scored, or worn (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401429">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1401429" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401429" filename="../figg14/G1401429.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Gear Surface Inspection</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect shafts for nicks or scores (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401430">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1401430" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401430" filename="../figg14/G1401430.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Shaft Surface Inspection</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
